<p><a name="Warlords" id="Warlords"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Chinese_Civil_War&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Warlords">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Warlords</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Zhang_Zuolin" title="Zhang Zuolin">Zhang Zuolin</a> (Killed in a train bombing by the Japanese, his son Zhang Xueliang took over his lands)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Zhang_Xueliang" title="Zhang Xueliang">Zhang Xueliang</a> (Son of Zhang Zuolin, in the <a href="/wiki/Xian_Incident" title="Xian Incident" class="mw-redirect">Xian Incident</a>, he and Yang Hu Cheng forced <a href="/wiki/Chiang_Kaishek" title="Chiang Kaishek" class="mw-redirect">Chiang Kaishek</a> to end his war against the Communists and ally with them against the Japanese. He was then jailed by Chiang until 1989.)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Feng_Yuxiang" title="Feng Yuxiang">Feng Yuxiang</a> (Changed his support to KMT in 1925, then fought them in 1930 <a href="/wiki/Central_Plains_War" title="Central Plains War">Central Plains War</a> and lost. Organized the <a href="/wiki/Chahar_People%27s_Anti-Japanese_Army" title="Chahar People's Anti-Japanese Army">Chahar People's Anti-Japanese Army</a> in cooperation with north China Communists and changed again to CPC in 1945 and visited the USSR).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yen_Hsi-shan" title="Yen Hsi-shan">Yen Hsi-shan</a> (Ruled <a href="/wiki/Shanxi" title="Shanxi">Shanxi</a> Province until 1948)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ma_clique" title="Ma clique">Ma clique</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Chen_Jitang" title="Chen Jitang">Chen Jitang</a></li>
</ul>
